Source: Collins Concise English Dictionary
Author:
Vol / Page: 637
Edition:
Quote: lay-by ... 4. Chiefly Austral. & N.Z. a system of payment whereby a buyer pays a deposit on an article, which is reserved for him until he has paid the full price.
Notes: 1986 NZPOD 424; 1985 Collins NZ Compact Dict. 279

